# Performance Analysis Plan

## Purpose

Summarize what DM4b will measure and why. Describe the design's
performance questions in a few sentences and name the target
documents this plan traces back to:

- `docs/spec.md`
- `docs/targets.md`
- `docs/analysis/decomposition.md`
- `docs/analysis/pipeline-mapping.md`
- `docs/test-plan/test-plan.md`

## Run-ID Scheme

Document the naming convention DM4b must use for recorded runs.
Keep it stable and deterministic.

Example:

- `baseline-<workload>`
- `sweep-<parameter>-<value>`
- `stress-<workload>-<variant>`

## Workload Justification

For each workload family DM4b will run, explain:

- which target rows it helps verify
- why it is representative
- whether it comes from the spec directly, from DM3 stress tests,
  or is an inferred analysis workload

